<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7710> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7710" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Monetalis. In MRR 2.439, and Index, 561, refer also to Crawford, RRC 1.326-327, no. 322, 102 B.C. Probably C. Fabius C. f Hadrianus (cf. ILLRP 363). In MRR 2.561, delete Buteo.[85]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7696> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7696" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praetor 85 or 84. In MRR 2.60, refer also to CIL 1(2).2.718-ILLRP 363.  Propraetor in Africa, until 82 (MRR 2.64, 69), but his death is dated probably late in 83 by Badian, Studies 72.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4120> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4120" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Propraetor in Africa (Oros. 5.20.3; cf. Ps.-Ascon. 241 Stangl). See 84, and 82, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4098> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4098" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. Per. 84, Praetor. Drove Metellus Pius out of Africa (Liv.; cf. Ps.-Ascon. 241 Stangl; see Promagistrates, on Metellus)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4097> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4097" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "1 The title Praetor in Livy may refer either to a magistracy in the city or to a prorogued command. Ps.-Asconius found his sources quite c onfused: ut alii aiunt legatus, ut alii putant vel pro praetore vel praetor." .
